5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to seafood products; to amend Sections
10 22-20A-3, 22-20A-5, 22-20A-7, and 22-20A-8, Code of Alabama
11 1975, to authorize the Commissioner of Agriculture and
12 Industries to test seafood to ensure compliance with country
13 of origin labeling requirements; to revise the permitted
14 methods by which certain food service establishments may
15 notify consumers of country of origin; to further provide for
16 food service establishments that violate these requirements;
17 and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the
18 existing code language to current style.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
20 Section 1. Sections 22-20A-3, 22-20A-5, 22-20A-7, and
21 22-20A-8, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as
22 follows:
23 "§22-20A-3
