130 "§22-20A-8
131 (a) Any food service establishment that violates this
132 article or the rules any rule adopted thereunder pursuant to
133 this article, after notice and a hearing, shall be subject to
134 civil penalties. The State Health Officer shall impose these
135 penalties on a graduated scale in accordance with the
136 following schedule for all violations within a 24-month
137 period:
138 (1) For a first offense, a written warning.
139 (2) For a second offense, a fine of one hundred dollars
140 ($100).
Page 5

($100).
